\cf2 With the technological evolution, new forms of interaction with computational devices have been researched as an attempt to make the human-computer interaction easier and friendlier. Nowadays, hardware devices that are capable of processing user's movement, gesture and touches, have been developed. In order to follow this new paradigm, the software has to deal with non-traditional issues, like gesture interpretation or even an unknown number of simultaneously users.\cf0 \
